HEADWORD: Drawbench
<hw>Draw"bench`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A machine in which strips of metal are drawn through a drawplate;
especially, one in which wire is thus made; -- also called <xex>drawing
bench</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

